## Why Rent Instead of Buy? (The Practical SME View)

We often talk to business owners in JB who are torn between renting and taking a hire purchase loan to buy. While we offer financing for purchases, sometimes rental is actually the better move for your cash flow.

### 1. Zero Maintenance Headaches
When you rent, the maintenance is usually the supplier's problem. In the salty, humid air of Pasir Gudang, machines can wear down fast. With a rental, if the forklift breaks down, you just call the supplier to fix it or swap it out.

### 2. Tax Benefits
Rental payments are generally treated as an operating expense (OPEX). This means you can often deduct the full rental amount from your taxable income, which is simpler than managing depreciation schedules for an owned asset.

### 3. Flexibility for Peak Seasons
Many JB businesses see spikes during festive seasons or major export windows. Rental allows you to add a few more units for three months and return them when things quiet down.

