## 3 Hidden Costs to Watch Out For

This is where the "trusted uncle" advice comes in. Don't just look at the monthly rate; look at these three things:

### 1. The "Wear and Tear" Clause
Check who pays for what. Usually, the supplier covers major repairs, but you might be responsible for "consumables" like tires, light bulbs, or damage caused by operator negligence. If your warehouse floor is rough, you'll go through tires fast—make sure you know who is paying for the replacements.

### 2. Overtime Charges
Some rental contracts in JB are based on an 8-hour shift or 200 hours per month. If your team is running double shifts to meet a deadline, you might get hit with a "heavy usage" surcharge. Always clarify this upfront.

### 3. Transport and Mobilization
Pasir Gudang to Senai is a long way. Some suppliers include transport in the first month’s rent; others charge for every trip. If you only need the forklift for a week, the transport cost can sometimes be as high as the rental itself!

