## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

### Do I need a special license to operate a rental forklift in JB?
Yes. Under Malaysian law (DOSH/JKKP), forklift operators should be trained and certified. Many rental companies in JB also offer "operator included" rentals if you don't have your own certified staff.

### Can I rent for just one day?
Yes, many suppliers in Johor Bahru offer daily rentals, especially for unloading specific shipments. However, when you factor in transport costs, daily rental is the most expensive way to do it.

### What happens if the forklift breaks down?
A reputable JB supplier should offer a 24-hour or same-day repair service. If the machine cannot be fixed on-site within a certain timeframe (usually 24-48 hours), they should provide a replacement unit.

